SLS 26RS-548 ORIGINAL
2026 Regular Session
SENATE BILL NO. 226
BY SENATOR LUNEAU
INSURANCE RATES. Prohibits insurance rate determination based on risks classified by
gender. (8/1/26)
1 AN ACT
2 To amend and reenact R.S. 22:1454(A), relative to rating standards and methods; to prohibit
3 rate classifications based on gender; and to provide for related matters.
4 Be it enacted by the Legislature of Louisiana:
5 Section 1. R.S. 22:1454(A) is hereby amended and reenacted to read as follows:
6 §1454. Rating standards and methods
7 A. Rates shall not be excessive, inadequate, or unfairly discriminatory. Risks
8 may be classified using any criteria except that no risk shall be classified on the basis
9 of race, gender, color, creed, or national origin.
